parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected cracking or shattering of the windshield can cause a significant distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle. In addition, the cracked or shattered windshield can obstruct the driver's vision, further increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: often without any apparent cause or warning; cracks may start small and spread rapidly; cracks may occur in the same location on the windshield
such as the passenger side or driver's side edge; windshield may crack or shatter even when parked or driven at low speeds.
